UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S030439320100054X
KW  - Expectations hypothesis
KW  - Changepoints
KW  - Breakpoints
KW  - Learning
AB  - This paper links the term structure to perceptions of monetary policy. Long-horizon forecasts of short rates required by no-arbitrage term structure models are heavily influenced by the endpoints, or limiting conditional forecasts, of the short rate process. Common assumptions that the short rate is mean-reverting or contains a unit root are shown to generate unrealistic yield predictions. Failures occur because these assumptions inadequately account for historical shifts in market perceptions of the policy target for inflation. This paper links endpoint shifts to agent learning about shifts in long-term policy goals. Shifting endpoints in short rate processes significantly improve yield predictions.
